result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Paul Hayes Freel not in court, in custody.  Attorney Joseph Thomas Domask in court for Paul Hayes Freel.  Prosecuting attorney James C Griffin in court for the State of Wisconsin. Status conference held, defense is requesting a plea and sentencing. Attorney Domask states that defendant has picked up another case. Case is adjourned in Branch 02.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 11, 2022 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Paul Hayes Freel in court with attorney Joseph Thomas Domask.  Gerald Henry Alder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Hearing held via Zoom. Defense requests a status conference date. Case adjourned, Branch 2.  Status conference scheduled for September 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Paul Hayes Freel in court by video with Attorney Joseph Thomas Domask who appears in person.  Defendant Paul Hayes Freel in custody.  Adam Joseph Best appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. Parties are advised that this case is assigned to Branch 02, Judge Childs. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court held colloquy with defendant. Probable cause has been found and the defendant is bound over for trial. Original Information e-filed, copy given to defense counsel who waived reading. Defense enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant. Case is adjourned to Br. 02.  Scheduling conference scheduled for August 1, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Paul Hayes Freel in court, in custody.  James C Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Hearing held via Zoom. Defendant requested court appointed counsel and agreed to reimburse Milwaukee County for the expense. Court found defendant is eligible for appointment of counsel. Court appoints attorney Joseph Domask, present in court, to represent defendant in this matter at County expense and at the rate of $100.00 per hour. The Court ordered the defendant repay the County at a rate of $50.00 per month beginning 09-01-2022, and then the 1st of each month there after. Court advised defendant failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Case adjourned for preliminary hearing, Branch PE.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 21, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Paul Hayes Freel in court, in custody, appear by video.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for preliminary hearing. Defendant appears without counsel.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 02.  Court orders the case adjourned for CAUSE for an Indigency Hearing. Next court date provided by Judge Childs clerk.  Indigency hearing scheduled for June 8, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Case scheduled for preliminary hearing on 06-02-2022 with other pending case with retained counsel. Court takes no action this day and orders case remain calendared for preliminary hearing.

Defendant Paul Hayes Freel not in court, defendant in custody.  ADA Hira appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminary hearing. States witness is present. Mr Freel is located in an isolation pod, unable to appear for court. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 2, 2022 at 01:30 pm.  Indigency hearing scheduled for May 31, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3.  The Court ordered defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.  Scram bracelet ordered to monitor defendant maintains absolute sobriety.

Defendant Paul Hayes Freel in court with attorney Kevin Michael Gaertner, as friend of court.  Defendant Paul Hayes Freel in custody.  Brad Alan Vorpahl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Paul Hayes Freel appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 02.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for May 16, 2022 at 08:30 am.
